!! This uses the US International Keyboard as its base.
!! The difference is that Alt_R becomes AltGr
!! For details on xmodmap:
!! https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Xmodmap#Modifier_keys
!! useful commands: xmodmap, xmodmap -pm, xmodmap $HOME/.Xmodmap,
!!     xmodmap -e "keycode ## = key1 key2 key3 key4 key5 key6 key7"
!! where each column refers to a keysym
!!    Key
!!    Shift+Key
!!    Mode_switch+Key
!!    Mode_switch+Shift+Key
!!    ISO_Level3_Shift+Key
!!    ISO_Level3_Shift+Shift+Key
!! Only the first four keysyms are really used by X servers.

keycode 66 = Hyper_R NoSymbol NoSymbol NoSymbol
clear lock
clear mod3
add mod3 = Hyper_R
